inlineContent.text: class is an abstract class. Don’t instantiate an
object directly. Instead, instantiate one of the following concrete subclasses:
class provides a convenience method to create each of these subclasses.
Like many HealthKit classes, HealthKit object types aren’t extensible. Don’t subclass these classes.
Additionally, wherever possible, this class uses a single instance to represent all copies of the same type. For example, if you make two calls to the
method with the same identifier, the system returns the same instance. Reusing object types helps reduce HealthKit’s overall memory usage.
